    <sec id="Sec9">
      <title>A large-scale statistical test using dynamic signals from small-scale feature selection</title>
      <p id="Par47">On a large scale, we study the variability of the high-order moments of each tetranucleotide and use dynamic signals selected by small-scale features to design iterations of large-scale statistical tests to identify large, multi-window segments (Fig. <xref rid="Fig3" ref-type="fig">3</xref>b).</p>
      <p id="Par48">To assess changes of local signatures surrounding the <italic>i</italic>th window, we choose 2τ window surrounding the <italic>i</italic>th window as its neighbourhood and calculate the normalised first, second, third and fourth standardized moments of each signature as follows:
