				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mathtt{\varphi}\left({\mathrm{f}}_{\mathrm{t}}^{\mathrm{i}}\right) $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M52" display="inline"><mml:mi mathvariant="monospace">φ</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:msubsup><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">f</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">t</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">i</mml:mi></mml:msubsup></mml:mfenced></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2020_3501_Article_IEq16.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> is a random indicator function defined as follows:
<disp-formula id="Equ10"><label>10</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M53">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mathtt{\varphi}\left({\mathrm{f}}_{\mathrm{t}}^{\mathrm{i}}\right)=\left\{\begin{array}{cc}0&amp; {\mathrm{f}}_{\mathrm{t}}^{\mathrm{i}}\in \left({\upvarphi}_{\mathrm{t}}^{-1}\left(\frac{\upalpha}{2}\right),{\upvarphi}_{\mathrm{t}}^{-1}\left(1-\frac{\upalpha}{2}\right)\right)\\ {}1&amp; \mathrm{Otherwise}\end{array}\right. $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M54" display="block"><mml:mi mathvariant="monospace">φ</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:msubsup><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">f</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">t</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">i</mml:mi></mml:msubsup></mml:mfenced><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mfenced close="" open="{"><mml:mtable columnalign="center"><mml:mtr><mml:mtd><mml:mn>0</mml:mn></mml:mtd><mml:mtd><mml:msubsup><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">f</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">t</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">i</mml:mi></mml:msubsup><mml:mo>∈</mml:mo><mml:mfenced close=")" open="(" separators=","><mml:mrow><mml:msubsup><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">φ</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">t</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mfrac><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">α</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:mfrac></mml:mfenced></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:msubsup><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">φ</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">t</mml:mi><mml:mrow><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:msubsup><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:mrow><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:mfrac><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">α</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:mfrac></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:mtd></mml:mtr><mml:mtr><mml:mtd><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mtd><mml:mtd><mml:mtext>Otherwise</mml:mtext></mml:mtd></mml:mtr></mml:mtable></mml:mfenced></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="12859_2020_3501_Article_Equ10.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula></p>
      <p id="Par52">φ<sub>t</sub> φ<sub>t</sub> is the cumulative kernel distribution function of the dynamic core signature f<sub>t</sub>, <inline-formula id="IEq17"><alternatives><tex-math id="M55">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
