    <sec id="Sec10">
      <title>Refine the boundaries of predicted GIs</title>
      <p id="Par54">For each multi-window region detected by the above method, we segment it into several different fragments based on the GC content deviation, and use the G-C deviation and Markovian Jensen-Shannon divergence (MJSD) to determine the boundaries of the predicted GIs. Assume <italic>t</italic><sub>1</sub> t1 and <italic>t</italic><sub>2</sub> are the start and end points of a given genomic island <inline-formula id="IEq18"><alternatives><tex-math id="M57">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {S}_{\left[{t}_1\to {t}_2\right]} $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M58" display="inline"><mml:msub><mml:mi>S</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close="]" open="["><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>→</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2020_3501_Article_IEq18.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> St1 → t2. We search its boundaries from the expanded region <inline-formula id="IEq19"><alternatives><tex-math id="M59">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {S}_{\left[{t}_1-\gamma kb\to {t}_2+\gamma kb\right]} $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M60" display="inline"><mml:msub><mml:mi>S</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close="]" open="["><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">γkb</mml:mi><mml:mo>→</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">γkb</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2020_3501_Article_IEq19.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> St1-γkb → t2 + γkb. G-C deviation is one of the important sequence features, describing the differences between DNA fragments [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR45">45</xref>, <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR46">46</xref>]. In order to find the starting position, the sequence St1-γkb → t2 is divided into different sub-sequences to get some points <inline-formula id="IEq20"><alternatives><tex-math id="M61">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \left\{{P}_{S_{\left[{t}_1-\gamma kb\to {t}_2\right]}}^{CG}\right\} $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M62" display="inline"><mml:mfenced close="}" open="{"><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>P</mml:mi><mml:msub><mml:mi>S</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close="]" open="["><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">γkb</mml:mi><mml:mo>→</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">CG</mml:mi></mml:msubsup></mml:mfenced></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2020_3501_Article_IEq20.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. For each point <italic>t</italic><sub><italic>τ</italic></sub>, its MJSD was calculatedStτ→t2 as follows:
<disp-formula id="Equ11"><label>11</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M63">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {\displaystyle \begin{array}{l}{MJSD}^2\left({t}_{\tau}\right)={H}^2\left({S}_{\left[{t}_1-\gamma kb\to {t}_2\right]}\right)-\frac{t_{\tau }-{t}_1-\gamma kb+1}{t_2-{t}_1-\gamma kb+1}{H}^2\left({S}_{\left[{t}_1-\gamma kb\to {t}_{\tau}\right]}\right)\\ {}\kern10em -\frac{t_2-{t}_{\tau }+1}{t_2-{t}_1-\gamma kb+1}{H}^2\left({S}_{\left[{t}_{\tau}\to {t}_2\right]}\right)\end{array}} $$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M64" display="block"><mml:mtable columnalign="left" displaystyle="true"><mml:mtr><mml:mtd><mml:msup><mml:mtext mathvariant="italic">MJSD</mml:mtext><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msup><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mi>τ</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mfenced><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:msup><mml:mi>H</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msup><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:msub><mml:mi>S</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close="]" open="["><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">γkb</mml:mi><mml:mo>→</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:msub></mml:mfenced><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:mfrac><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mi>τ</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">γkb</mml:mi><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">γkb</mml:mi><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:mfrac><mml:msup><mml:mi>H</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msup><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:msub><mml:mi>S</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close="]" open="["><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">γkb</mml:mi><mml:mo>→</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mi>τ</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:msub></mml:mfenced></mml:mtd></mml:mtr><mml:mtr><mml:mtd><mml:mspace width="10em"/><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:mfrac><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mi>τ</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub><mml:mo>−</mml:mo><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">γkb</mml:mi><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:mfrac><mml:msup><mml:mi>H</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msup><mml:mfenced close=")" open="("><mml:msub><mml:mi>S</mml:mi><mml:mfenced close="]" open="["><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mi>τ</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>→</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mn>2</mml:mn></mml:msub></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:msub></mml:mfenced></mml:mtd></mml:mtr></mml:mtable></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="12859_2020_3501_Article_Equ11.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula>where H2St1-γkb → tτ and H2Stτ → t2are the entropies of the <inline-formula id="IEq21"><alternatives><tex-math id="M65">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
